  "prompt": "How do I check my last 3 charges in Vodafone?",
  "response": "If you want to check your last three charges on your Vodafone account, you can generally follow these steps:\n\n1. **Via the My Vodafone App:**\n   - Download the My Vodafone App from the App Store (iOS) or Google Play Store (Android), if you haven't already.\n   - Open the app and log in with your Vodafone account details.\n   - Navigate to the billing section or statement section within the app.\n   - Look for recent transactions or charges listed there.\n\n2. **Using Vodafone Website:**\n   - Go to the Vodafone website and log in to your account.\n   - Find the billing or account section.\n   - View your recent transactions or download your statements which should reflect the last few charges.\n\n3. **Customer Service:**\n   - If you're unable to find the information online or through the app, you can contact Vodafone customer service directly.\n   - You can do this via phone, live chat, or visiting a Vodafone store.\n   - Provide your account details and request information about your recent charges/transactions.\n\n4. **Text or USSD Code (if available in your region):**\n   - Some regions allow users to send a specific text or dial a USSD code to get account information.\n   - Check Vodafone's website for your region or contact customer service to find out the specific text message code or USSD code you need to use.\n\nRemember to have your account information ready when checking charges, especially when contacting customer service.",
